    <h1>CLASSES Cre&#xAD;at&#xAD;ing Videos For So&#xAD;cial Me&#xAD;dia</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201016/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-16"><time>2020-10-16</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Bul­let Jour­nal­ing</p>
    <p>In this vir­tual work­shop, learn to in­put monthly spreads, weekly and daily logs, time­lines, habit track­ers and timelog ex­er­cise by us­ing bul­let jour­nal­ing. It is de­signed to help you de­velop dis­ci­pline and aware­ness of your feel­ings and hope­fully aid in the over­all reg­u­la­tion of your emo­tions. Do­na­tions are wel­come and will go to­wards sus­tain­ing ini­tia­tives at arts and cul­tural cen­tre Hill­side 1820. Or­gan­ised by TRCL, a non-profit that har­vests the po­ten­tial of arts and cul­ture.</p>
    <p>WHEN: To­day, 7.30 - 9pm</p>
    <p>AD­MIS­SION: Free with reg­is­tra­tion INFO: str.sg/J6ZT</p>
    <p>Par­tic­i­pants will learn the dif­fer­ent styles com­monly used to cre­ate on­line con­tent and how to struc­ture it to ef­fec­tively com­mu­ni­cate their mes­sage to their au­di­ence. They will learn what is needed in each of the fol­low­ing stages – pre-pro­duc­tion, pro­duc­tion and post-pro­duc­tion – and how to con­cep­tu­alise, shoot and edit sim­ple videos. Com­mis­sioned by the Na­tional Arts Coun­cil Sin­ga­pore for self-em­ployed peo­ple in the arts sec­tor or em­ploy­ees of arts or­gan­i­sa­tions.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Nov 2, 10am, & Nov 3, 10am AD­MIS­SION: Free with reg­is­tra­tion INFO: str.sg/J6Z5</p>


